rules.to: /* returns an array of	     { "x" : date_in_ms,	       "y" : average_number_of_cases }	*/	( $subset := COVID19BE_CASES_AGESEX[     PROVINCE = $$.PROVINCE 	                                      and AGEGROUP = $$.AGEGROUP	                                      and SEX      = $$.SEX].{ "date_int" : $toMillis(DATE)/(24*60*60*1000),	                                                               "cases"  : CASES};	  $first_day := $subset.date_int~>$min();	  $last_day := $subset.date_int~>$max();	  [ $first_day ..  ( $last_day -AVERAGE_PERIOD+1)].(	      $start_period :=$;	      $end_period   :=$start_period + $$.AVERAGE_PERIOD -1;	      $sum_cases    := $subset[ date_int >= $start_period and date_int <= $end_period].cases~>$sum();	      {	     "x" : ($start_period + $end_period )*24*60*60*1000/2,	     "y" :$sum_cases~>$exists()?$sum_cases/($$.AVERAGE_PERIOD): 0	     })	)
